translated: Bonde, Claes Gösta Yngve, district land surveyor, Skövde, born on November 25th, 1901 in Kalmar to Claes and Hanna B. G. Married to Agnies Andensison in 1930. Children: Claes-Gö-ran born in 1931, Birgitta in 1934, Anders in 1936, and Lars-Oliof in 1941. He completed his high school diploma in Kalmar in 1920, obtained his land surveying degree in 1926, and his agricultural engineering degree in 1930. He was a second lieutenant in 1938, a first captain in 1943, and a reserve captain from 1944. He worked as a land surveyor in Växjö in 1926, in Södertälje in 1926, as an assistant at the land surveying office in Mariestad in 1930, as a land surveyor in Lidköping in 1933, and as a district land surveyor in Skövde from 1939. He was a property assessor for land measurements in Tibro, Karlsborg, and Stenstorp from 1940. He was the chairman of the Skövde vocational educational association from 1943 and the technical association from 1946, as well as the parents' association of the school from 1945. He was a member of the Skaraborg vocational education association and a first-year member in the shooting club.
